    {
      "id": "1442707767956738179",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2025-11-25T02:45:36.095+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "@tnt I agree with you that this rule looks incorrect.\n\nCurrently it's\n```\nnp12_l1 = nplus.interacting(nplus_edges.separation(pgate.edges.and(pcomp_edges), 0.32.um, euclidian).polygons(0.001.um))\n```\nwhich is (almost) nplus within 0.32um of pgate.\n\nA different rule might be\n```\nnp12_l1 = nplus.interacting(pgate.sized(0.32.um, size_inside(poly2), steps(3)))\n```\nThe minimum poly2 spacing is 0.24um, which means sizing by 0.12um or greater can merge polygons. By splitting into 3 steps, we ensure that each growth will be about 0.11um < 0.12um.",
      "author": {
        "id": "738396032295108721",
        "name": "bailey8889",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "bailey",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "2025-11_media/0-EB806.png"
      },
