    {
      "id": "1442787868941750336",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2025-11-25T08:03:53.658+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "I agree with the interpretation of the rule here.\n@bailey's rule implementation looks correct to me. Thanks a lot!\n\nHowever, if we just want the gate extension as specified in the rule, we might want to remove the pgate after the sizing:\n\n```\nnp12_l1 = nplus.interacting(pgate.sized(0.32.um, size_inside(poly2), steps(3)).not(pgate))\n```\n\nNot sure if that makes any difference here. What would you opt for?\n\nI'll try both implementations on a chip design to see if there are any regressions.",
      "author": {
        "id": "323371864074485771",
        "name": "mole99",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Leo Moser (mole99)",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [
          {
            "id": "1423020172595298314",
            "name": "Mod",
